There is a commotion in the Mpape area of Abuja on Saturday as a team of soldiers and policemen stopped a gang of armed robbers who had broken into a first generation bank. It was learnt that the robbers had gained entry into the bank when the security operatives arrived at the scene. According to reports, the armed robbers had refused to vacate the premises of the bank after one of them was shot at when he attempted to escape. See photos: Photos/PUNCH: Olatunji Obasa        